  "title": "Coefficient of (Reflex) Luminous Intensity",
  "parse": {
    "text": "<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><p><b>2-1-160</b>\n</p><p>Quotient of the luminous intensity reflected in the direction considered, divided by the illuminance at the retro-reflector for given angles of entrance, observation and rotation.\n</p><p><br>\nNote: In the photometry of retro-reflectors, this coefficient is designated by the abbreviation <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0d61f8370cad1d412f80b84d143e1257\">C</span>.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"dd7536794b63bf90eccfd37f9b147d7f\">I</span>.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"d20caec3b48a1eef164cb4ca81ba2587\">L</span>. It is usually expressed in millicandelas per lux (mcd/lx).\n</p><p>Reference: <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0d61f8370cad1d412f80b84d143e1257\">C</span>.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"dd7536794b63bf90eccfd37f9b147d7f\">I</span>.<span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"3a3ea00cfc35332cedf6e5e9a32e94da\">E</span>.\n</p><p><br>\n<br>\n<br>\n<i>Please note that this is the term as it stands in the original <span class=\"mw-lingo-term\" data-lingo-term-id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\">IALA</span> Dictionary edition (1970-1989)</i>\n<br>\n</p>\n<div class=\"LanguageLinks\">\n<table width=\"100%\">\n<tbody><tr valign=\"top\" style=\"background: #FFFFFF\">\n<td style=\"width: 25px; padding-left: 0em; border-right: 1px solid #aaaaaa;border-left: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-top: 1px solid #EEF3E2;border-bottom: 1px solid #EEF3E2;\"><span typeof=\"mw:File\"><a href=\"/wiki/dictionary/index.php/File:25px-Geographylogo.png\" class=\"mw-file-description\" title=\"Languages\"><img alt=\"Languages\" src=\"/wiki/dictionary/images/8/82/25px-Geographylogo.png\" decoding=\"async\" width=\"25\" height=\"25\" class=\"mw-file-element\"></a></span></td>\n<td style=\"padding: 1px 1em 0; background: #EEF3E2;\">\n<p><b><a class=\"mw-selflink selflink\">English</a></b>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n<span></span>\n</p>\n</td></tr></tbody></table></div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0d61f8370cad1d412f80b84d143e1257\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Contrast\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Celsius (previously Centigrade)\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Capacitance\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"dd7536794b63bf90eccfd37f9b147d7f\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>charge current\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Intensity\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"d20caec3b48a1eef164cb4ca81ba2587\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Luminance\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Level (technician training - WWA)\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Latitude (in degrees)\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"3a3ea00cfc35332cedf6e5e9a32e94da\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Illuminance\n</p>\n</div></div><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>Energy\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div><div class=\"mw-lingo-tooltip\" id=\"0a1217bfe27a54fc7e55b72fc62c2371\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition navigation-not-searchable\"><div class=\"mw-lingo-definition-text\">\n<p>International Association of Marine Aids to Navigation and Lighthouse Authorities - AISM\n</p>\n</div></div>\n</div>\n<!-- \nNewPP limit report\nCached time: 20260615184135\nCache expiry: 86400\nReduced expiry: false\nComplications: []\nCPU time usage: 0.045 seconds\nReal time usage: 0.053 seconds\nPreprocessor visited node count: 60/1000000\nPost‐expand include size: 911/2097152 bytes\nTemplate argument size: 554/2097152 bytes\nHighest expansion depth: 7/100\nExpensive parser function count: 4/100\nUnstrip recursion depth: 0/20\nUnstrip post‐expand size: 0/5000000 bytes\n-->\n<!--\nTransclusion expansion time report (%,ms,calls,template)\n100.00%   13.552      1 -total\n 75.48%   10.229      1 Template:Languages\n 53.09%    7.195      4 Template:Languages/Lang\n 23.61%    3.199      1 Template:IALAFooter\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key wiki_iala_dictionary_1_41:pcache:idhash:418-0!canonical and timestamp 20260615184135 and revision id 9147. Rendering was triggered because: diff-page\n -->\n</div>",
