  "wikitext": "\n'''2-1-160\n\nQuotient of the luminous intensity reflected in the direction considered, divided by the illuminance at the retro-reflector for given angles of entrance, observation and rotation.\n\n\nNote: In the photometry of retro-reflectors, this coefficient is designated by the abbreviation C.I.L. It is usually expressed in millicandelas per lux (mcd/lx).\n\nReference: C.I.E.\n\n{{IALAFooter}}\n\n{{languages|Coefficient of (Reflex) Luminous Intensity}}\n[[Category:2.1 Optics and Vision]]\n[[Category:Alphabetical Index]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 1970-89 Edition]]\n[[Category:IALA Dictionary 2023 Revision]]"
